{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": \"Task after git init\", \"role\": \"user\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"I'll help you understand what comes after `git init`. Let me first check the current state of your repository to provide context-specific guidance.\", \"type\": \"text\"}, {\"id\": \"toolu_01FfWmH18PJrecsBY32ihvrR\", \"input\": {\"command\": \"pwd\", \"description\": \"Check current directory\"}, \"name\": \"Bash\", \"type\": \"tool_use\"}, {\"id\": \"toolu_01LL7D7U9dohr3kze9jmZNym\", \"input\": {\"command\": \"ls -la\", \"description\": \"List all files including hidden\"}, \"name\": \"Bash\", \"type\": \"tool_use\"}, {\"id\": \"toolu_014JZ82YqnUSudebuZgHnHCB\", \"input\": {\"command\": \"git status\", \"description\": \"Check git repository status\"}, \"name\": \"Bash\", \"type\": \"tool_use\"}], \"role\": \"assistant\"}], \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929", "id": "msg_01Lb3TuRkzJ2zVKPyoR2QLsy", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "I can see you have a git repository initialized and you're on `branch_1` with an initial commit already made. Here's what typically comes after `git init`:\n\n## Standard Git Workflow After `git init`:\n\n1. **Create/Add files** - Create your project files\n2. **Stage changes** - `git add <files>` or `git add .` to stage all files\n3. **Make your first commit** - `git commit -m \"Initial commit\"` (you've already done this!)\n4. **Set up remote** (optional) - `git remote add origin <remote-url>`\n5. **Push to remote** (optional) - `git push -u origin <branch>`\n\n## Your Current Situation:\n\nYou've already completed the initial commit. Your next steps would typically be:\n\n1. **Start working** - Create or modify files for your project\n2. **Stage and commit changes** - As you work:\n   ```bash\n   git add <files>\n   git commit -m \"Description of changes\" --trailer \"Co-authored-by: Sculptor <sculptor@imbue.com>\"\n   ```\n3. **Create branches** - For new features:\n   ```bash\n   git checkout -b feature-name\n   ```\n\n**Note**: Since this is a Sculptor sandbox environment, you don't have access to push to a remote repository directly. If you need to sync changes, you can use the Sculptor merge workflow.\n\nWhat would you like to do next with your repository?"}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 8, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 3813, "cache_read_input_tokens": 12180, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 3813, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 337, "service_tier": "standard"}}}
